Credit to• @wearebreitbart Several women have taken to TikTok to join the “Burn Bra Challenge” to destroy their NIKE @nike sports bras after the sportswear giant hired transgender activist Dylan Mulvaney @dylanmulvaney to flog the company’s sports bras and leggings.

A TikTok user calling herself “chatterbox.mama,” and who also describes herself as a “southern mama,” posted her “Burn Bra Challenge” on Tuesday in which she is seen setting a NIKE women’s sports top on fire as she tells viewers that she is “sick and tired” of the company pushing women around, the New York Post reported. “All you real women out there – we are in the fight of all fights,” the woman said to her more than 140,000 followers.

“Since the 1960s, we have been fighting for the right to be women,” she added. “Nike, you should be ashamed of yourself.”

“NIKE, you should be ashamed of yourself. You chose a little boy with no breasts and some junk in his pants to represent real women,” she said, adding, “Nike, I am done with you.”

“I will never, ever buy a Nike product for as long as I live,” she said. “And there are millions and millions and millions of women just like me.”

She then challenged other women to “burn your Nike bras … as a way of showing our solidarity and how serious we are that we will be recognized.”

“We are the queens, your consumers hit you where it hurts, and that’s right in your pocket,” she said, concluding, “I challenge every real woman that is sick of this nonsense. It’s a great night to burn my Nike bras.”

“They’re pushing us around and we’re not doing anything about it!”

She then burned two bras next to her outdoor pool.

👀 Did you know this?! Video from • @distant.ffa In 1996, Nike Sports Entertainment introduced Swoosh, a superhero mascot designed by the creators of Val Kilmer’s Batman suit. The character, equipped with a $125,000 costume, made its debut at the Hoop Heroes event in Tokyo, performing stunts to entertain the crowd.

Although Swoosh found popularity in Japan, it didn’t garner much attention in the United States. Ultimately, due to an economic downturn, Nike Sports Entertainment ceased operations and the character of Swoosh was retired.

🔈ANNOUNCENT🥹🔈 
Hello everyone!

I hope you all are doing great! Today, I want to share some important news with you. I have decided to take a break from Instagram to prioritize my children, nurture my relationship with my husband, and deepen my spiritual connection with Christ.  I need to address my neglected mental, social, emotional, and spiritual well-being.

In this fast-paced digital world, it’s important to step back and focus on what truly matters in life.  Family is an important foundation, and I believe that investing quality time and energy into these relationships is paramount. Additionally, my spiritual relationship with Christ is a guiding force that brings fulfillment and purpose.

Art and creativity hold a special place in my heart. Through them, I have discovered the beauty of self-expression and the ability to touch others’ lives. However, it is essential to remember that Christ is the ultimate source of all inspiration and fulfillment. He is the giver of gifts, including the creative talents we possess.

During this break, I will be embracing moments of introspection, diving deeper into my relationship with my family, Christ, and the creativity that flows from His abundant blessings. 

I want to express my sincere gratitude for your unwavering support and love throughout my Instagram journey. Your feedback and encouragement have uplifted me. It’s been awesome to share everyone’s talents with the world!

Remember, life is about finding balance and staying true to our values. I believe that this break will help me realign with what matters most, and allow me to share everyone’s authentic and inspiring content in the future.

Thank you for your understanding and continued support. Take care, enjoy appreciating your loved ones, and may your own creative journeys be blessed abundantly by the giver of all, Christ.

Joyfully,

HJ

Step 1. Clean uppers of AF1s with Soft/Medium Brush 
Step 2. Clean Midsoles/Soles with Stiff Brush 
Step 3. Use Laundry Bag Kit (optional). I only use the laundry bag to clean my laces, but you can throw the whole pair and laces in the bag and use the laundry cleaner. 
Step 4. Use Sole Revive on the soles and place under ☀️Sunlight or a UV light. (Hack: use peroxide and baking soda mixture and place under UV light if you are cheap like me—does not work as well and you’ll need to do it 2-3x but it’s cheaper 😜)
Step 5. Wipe off Sole revive and enjoy your shoes!

You can also then remove creases and use touch up paint if they aren’t quite perfect. Hope this helps!

Base Shoe: 2019 Travis Scott × Air Jordan 1 Low ‘Mocha’
Travis Scott and Jordan Brand collaborate on an Air Jordan 1 Low, taking similar design cues from the high-top version. An oversized backward facing Swoosh is featured prominently on the lateral side of the shoe, while a regular Swoosh graces the medial side. Black and Dark Mocha nubuck dominate the upper, with a few pops of University Red adding a nice contrast. Travis Scott details are subtly placed on the shoe, with the
‘Cactus Jack’ logo appearing on the tongue, medial side panel and sockliner. The back heel tabs feature intricately stitched logos, with the Air Jordan Wings on the right shoe and Scott’s crudely drawn face on the left shoe.
